        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 4 at 5:38PM CDT until August 4 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mccook, moving
southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
San Manuel, Linn, Faysville, Edinburg North High School, Red Gate,
Edinburg South Texas International Airport
Edinburg South Texas International Airport, and Mcallen.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
